text: Kelly Elizabeth Parsons (born January 23, 1964, in Coral Gables, Florida) is a former American actress and model. She won the Our Little Miss pageant in 1975, which led to her being chosen as one of the Mouseketeers in the 1977–79 revival of The New Mickey Mouse Club and following this she attended Emerson Elementary School in Miami with her sister Kim. She also appeared in the films Evils of the Night and The Night Stalker and in episodes of the TV series Quincy, M.E. and Alice. She was Miss California USA in 1986 and one of the finalists for Miss USA. Her last national television appearance was on Star Search in 1986. She has since left show business. ==Biography== Parsons was born in Coral Gables, Florida, the daughter of Jesse Parsons and Joan Charlton. ==Filmography== {| class="wikitable" ! Year ! Title !
